## 2.5 Real-World Engineering Utility

> [!NOTE]
> **Industry Relevance Box:**
> - **Inner Classes** are heavily used in **GUI frameworks** (e.g., `ActionListener` implementations in Swing/AWT are anonymous inner classes), in **Collections** (e.g., `Map.Entry` is a static nested interface), and in **Builder design patterns**.
> - **Inheritance** underpins almost every Java framework — `Spring`, `Hibernate`, `Servlet API`, `JavaFX` — all built on class hierarchies.
> - **The `super` keyword** is essential for **template method patterns**, where parent algorithms are extended (not replaced) by subclasses.
