## 3.2 Complete Worked Example — Inheritance with `super`

```java
// File: VehicleDemo.java

// ─── SUPER CLASS (Parent) ─────────────────────────────────
class Vehicle {
    protected String brand = "Generic";   // protected → accessible to subclass
    protected int year = 2020;

    // Default constructor
    public Vehicle() {
        System.out.println("Vehicle() default constructor called");
    }

    // Parameterized constructor
    public Vehicle(String brand, int year) {
        this.brand = brand;
        this.year = year;
        System.out.println("Vehicle(brand, year) parameterized called");
    }

    // Method to be overridden
    public void start() {
        System.out.println("Vehicle starting... generic ignition");
    }

    public void honk() {
        System.out.println("Generic honk!");
    }
}

// ─── SUB CLASS (Child) ─────────────────────────────────────
class Car extends Vehicle {
    private String model;
    private int doors;

    public Car() {
        // Compiler AUTOMATICALLY inserts super() here
        // → calls Vehicle() — prints "Vehicle() default constructor called"
        this.model = "Sedan";
        this.doors = 4;
        System.out.println("Car() default constructor called");
    }

    public Car(String brand, int year, String model, int doors) {
        // EXPLICIT super() — MUST be first statement
        super(brand, year);                              // (1) super() constructor call
        this.model = model;
        this.doors = doors;
        System.out.println("Car(...) parameterized constructor called");
    }

    // Override start()
    @Override
    public void start() {
        super.start();                                   // (2) super.method() call
        System.out.println("Car engine purrs smoothly");
    }

    public void displaySpecs() {
        System.out.println("Brand: " + super.brand);     // (3) super.field access
        System.out.println("Year: " + year);             // inherited directly
        System.out.println("Model: " + model);
        System.out.println("Doors: " + doors);
        super.honk();                                    // calling parent's honk()
    }
}

// ─── DRIVER CLASS ─────────────────────────────────────────
public class VehicleDemo {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("--- Creating default Car ---");
        Car c1 = new Car();
        c1.displaySpecs();

        System.out.println("\n--- Creating parameterized Car ---");
        Car c2 = new Car("Toyota", 2023, "Camry", 4);
        c2.start();
        c2.displaySpecs();
    }
}
```

**Expected Output:**
```
--- Creating default Car ---
Vehicle() default constructor called
Car() default constructor called
Brand: Generic
Year: 2020
Model: Sedan
Doors: 4
Generic honk!

--- Creating parameterized Car ---
Vehicle(brand, year) parameterized called
Car(...) parameterized constructor called
Car engine purrs smoothly
Brand: Toyota
Year: 2023
Model: Camry
Doors: 4
Generic honk!
```

**Step-by-Step Logical Deduction:**

1. **Step 1 — Default constructor path:** `new Car()` → compiler auto-inserts `super()` → `Vehicle()` prints first → then `Car()` body executes. **Order: parent → child.**
2. **Step 2 — Parameterized constructor path:** `new Car("Toyota", ...)` → explicit `super(brand, year)` → `Vehicle(String, int)` matches → prints → then `Car(...)` body.
3. **Step 3 — `super.start()`:** Inside overridden `Car.start()`, calling `super.start()` invokes **parent's** version first, then `Car` adds its own behavior. This is **extension**, not replacement.
4. **Step 4 — `super.brand`:** Even though `brand` is inherited and accessible, writing `super.brand` makes the reference **explicit** — useful when `Car` also had its own `brand` field that shadowed it.

---

## 3.3 Analytical Matrix — When to Use What

| Scenario | Best Tool | Reason |
|----------|-----------|--------|
| Helper class used by **only one** outer class | **Member Inner Class** | Logical grouping, full access |
| Helper class **independent** of outer instance | **Static Nested Class** | Memory efficient, simpler instantiation |
| Helper class needed **only inside one method** | **Local Inner Class** | Scope minimization |
| **One-off** interface implementation | **Anonymous Inner Class** | Inline, no boilerplate |
| Need to **specialize** an existing class | **Inheritance (`extends`)** | Reuse + polymorphism |
| Need to **initialize parent** explicitly | **`super(args)`** | Custom parent initialization |
| Need to **extend parent's behavior** | **`super.method()`** | Open-closed principle |
| Need to **disambiguate same-named fields** | **`super.field`** | Resolve shadowing |
