### **Q1. [KTU University Exam – May 2024]**
**Differentiate between a Member Inner Class and a Static Nested Class in Java. Give one example of each.**

**Model Answer:**

| Feature | Member Inner Class | Static Nested Class |
|---------|--------------------|--------------------|
| Declaration | Non-static class inside another class | `static class` inside another class |
| Outer instance | **Required** — implicit reference | **Not required** |
| Access to outer | All members (including private) | Only **static** members |
| Instantiation | `outerObj.new Inner()` | `new Outer.Nested()` |
| Memory | Holds outer reference (heavier) | No outer reference (lighter) |

**Example:**

```java
class Outer {
    class Member {}           // Member Inner
    static class Nested {}    // Static Nested
}

// Driver:
Outer o = new Outer();
Outer.Member m = o.new Member();        // needs outer obj
Outer.Nested n = new Outer.Nested();    // no outer obj needed
```

