## 5.3 Topic Recap & Important Things to Remember

> [!NOTE]
> **Rapid-Revision Checklist (Print this before the exam!):**

### **Inner Classes — Must-Know Points**
- ⭐ Java has **four** inner class types: Member, Static Nested, Local, Anonymous.
- ⭐ Member inner class: **`outerObj.new Inner()`** — needs outer instance.
- ⭐ Static nested class: **`new Outer.Nested()`** — no outer instance.
- ⭐ Local inner class: lives **inside a method**, dies at method exit.
- ⭐ Anonymous inner class: **one-shot**, no name, used for inline interface implementation.
- ⭐ Inner classes can access **`final` or effectively final** local variables from the enclosing method.
- ⭐ Member inner classes hold an implicit **`OuterClass.this`** reference.

### **Inheritance — Must-Know Points**
- ⭐ Java supports **single inheritance** for classes via `extends`.
- ⭐ Java supports **multiple inheritance via interfaces** via `implements`.
- ⭐ Inheritance creates an **IS-A** relationship (compiler-enforced).
- ⭐ `protected` members are accessible to **subclasses in any package**.
- ⭐ Constructors are **not inherited** but can be invoked via `super()`.
- ⭐ Access modifiers can be **widened** in subclass (not narrowed).

### **`super` Keyword — Must-Know Points**
- ⭐ Three uses: `super()`, `super.field`, `super.method()`.
- ⭐ `super()` **must be the first statement** in a constructor.
- ⭐ If no `super()` written, compiler **auto-inserts** no-arg `super()`.
- ⭐ `super.method()` is used to **extend** parent's overridden behavior.
- ⭐ `super.field` resolves **field shadowing**.

### **High-Frequency KTU Traps**
- 🚫 `final` classes cannot be extended; `final` methods cannot be overridden.
- 🚫 `private` members are **not** inherited (though accessible in same class).
- 🚫 Static methods are **hidden**, not overridden (no runtime polymorphism).
- 🚫 Constructor of an abstract class **is called** when subclass is instantiated.

### **Mnemonics for Last-Minute Recall**
- 🎯 **"MASH"** → **M**ember, **A**nonymous, **S**tatic, **H**mm... wait — proper order is **Member → Static → Local → Anonymous**.
- 🎯 **"SFM"** → `super()` constructor, `super.field`, `super.method()`.
- 🎯 **"Cannot Skip Must Not Place"** → `super()` cannot skip parent constructors; must not place after other statements.
