> - **Common Mistake 2**: Confusing Java's `protected` (package + subclass) with C++'s `protected` (subclass only). In Part B comparison questions, failing to mention the **package-level access** of Java loses **2 marks**.
> - **Common Mistake 3**: Forgetting to show that `protected` members are still inaccessible from `main()` even when inherited. Always demonstrate this with a commented-out line in your code — examiners reward this with **extra clarity marks**.
