**Q2. [KTU University Exam – Dec 2022]**
**Explain the role of `addActionListener()` in a `JTextField` with an example.**

**Model Answer (3 marks):**

The `addActionListener(ActionListener l)` method registers an `ActionListener` with a `JTextField` so that the listener's `actionPerformed` method is invoked when the user presses the **Enter key** while focus is in the text field.

Example:

```java
JTextField tf = new JTextField(20);
tf.addActionListener(e -> System.out.println("Enter pressed: " + tf.getText()));
```

When the user types text and presses Enter, the lambda (treated as an `ActionListener`) executes and prints the text.

