**Model Solution (a) — 7 marks:**

The inheritance chain of `JTextField`:

`java.lang.Object` → `java.awt.Component` → `java.awt.Container` → `javax.swing.JComponent` → `javax.swing.text.JTextComponent` → `javax.swing.JTextField`

| Class | Role |
|---|---|
| `Object` | Root of all Java classes; provides `toString`, `equals`, `hashCode` |
| `Component` | Adds position, size, painting, and event handling base support |
| `Container` | Extends `Component` to allow other components to be added as children |
| `JComponent` | Swing base class; provides pluggable look-and-feel, borders, tooltips, double buffering |
| `JTextComponent` | Provides text model (`Document`), text editing, and selection support |
| `JTextField` | Specializes as a **single-line** editable text input |

---

**Model Solution (b) — 7 marks:**

```java
import javax.swing.*;
import java.awt.*;
import java.awt.event.*;

public class CharCountDemo extends JFrame {
    JTextField textField;
    JLabel countLabel;

    public CharCountDemo() {
        setTitle("Character Counter");
        setSize(350, 120);
        setLayout(new FlowLayout());
        setDefaultCloseOperation(JFrame.EXIT_ON_CLOSE);

        textField = new JTextField(20);
        countLabel = new JLabel("Characters typed: 0");

        textField.addKeyListener(new KeyAdapter() {
            @Override
            public void keyReleased(KeyEvent e) {
                int count = textField.getText().length();
                countLabel.setText("Characters typed: " + count);
            }
        });

        add(textField);
        add(countLabel);
        setVisible(true);
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        new CharCountDemo();
    }
}
```

**Explanation (for partial marks):**
- `KeyAdapter` is used instead of `KeyListener` to avoid implementing all three methods.
- `keyReleased` is overridden; it runs after every key release.
- `getText().length()` computes the character count.
- `setText` updates the label in real time.

