## 5. KTU 2024 Scheme Examination Question Bank & Topic Recap

### Part A Questions (3 Marks Each)

**Q1. `[KTU University Exam – May 2024]`** Define the Delegation Event Model in Java. List its three main components.

**Model Answer (3 Marks):**
The Delegation Event Model is an event-handling mechanism in Java in which the responsibility for processing an event generated by a GUI component is **delegated** (transferred) to a separate listener object, decoupling the source from the handler.

The three main components are:
1. **Event Source** — the GUI component (e.g., `JButton`) that generates the event.
2. **Event Object** — the object (e.g., `ActionEvent`) that encapsulates information about the event.
3. **Event Listener** — the object (e.g., an `ActionListener` implementation) that receives the event and handles it.

---

**Q2. `[KTU University Exam – Dec 2023]`** What is the difference between a listener interface and an adapter class in the Delegation Event Model? Give one example of each.

**Model Answer (3 Marks):**
A **listener interface** (e.g., `MouseListener`) declares abstract methods for handling events. Any class that implements it **must** override **all** declared methods, even if some are not needed.

An **adapter class** (e.g., `MouseAdapter`) provides **empty default implementations** of all methods declared in the corresponding listener interface. A class that extends an adapter can override **only** the methods it needs, leaving the rest as no-ops.

**Example:** `MouseListener` is an interface with 5 abstract methods; `MouseAdapter` is a class that implements `MouseListener` with empty method bodies, allowing selective overriding.

---

### Part B Questions (14 Marks Each — KTU Internal Choice Pattern)

