### Topic Recap & Important Things to Remember (Rapid Revision Checklist)

- The **Delegation Event Model** delegates event processing from the **source** to a separate **listener** via an **EventObject**.
- All event classes inherit from `java.util.EventObject` → `java.awt.AWTEvent` → specific event subclasses.
- The three **core components** are: **Event Source**, **Event Object**, **Event Listener**.
- The four steps to implement DEM are: **Create Source → Implement Listener Interface → Create Listener Object → Register with Source**.
- The registration method **always** follows the pattern `addXxxListener(listenerObject)`.
- `ActionListener` has **one** method: `actionPerformed(ActionEvent e)`.
- `MouseListener` has **five** methods: `mouseClicked`, `mousePressed`, `mouseReleased`, `mouseEntered`, `mouseExited`.
- `KeyListener` has **three** methods: `keyTyped`, `keyPressed`, `keyReleased`.
- `WindowListener` has **seven** methods covering opening, closing, activation, deactivation, iconification, and deiconification.
- **Adapter classes** (e.g., `MouseAdapter`, `KeyAdapter`, `WindowAdapter`) provide **empty default implementations** so you override only what you need. There is **no `ActionAdapter`** and **no `ItemAdapter`** because their interfaces have only one method.
- A single source can have **multiple** listeners; a single listener can serve **multiple** sources.
- `e.getSource()` returns the originating component; `e.getID()` returns an integer event-type ID.
- The **Event Dispatch Thread (EDT)** is responsible for invoking listener methods; use `SwingUtilities.invokeLater()` to ensure thread-safe GUI creation.
- The Delegation Event Model follows the **Observer Design Pattern** and is fully compatible with **JavaBeans**.

